import numpy as np
In [16]:
outliers = {}
for i in range(len(column_names)):
    q1 = merge[column_names[i]].quantile(0.25)
    q3 = merge[column_names[i]].quantile(0.75)
    
    upper = q3 + (q3-q1)*1.5
    
    outliers_count = np.sum(merge[column_names[i]] > upper)
    outliers[column_names[i]] = outliers_count

In [26]:
estimator = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=2023)
models = []
Scores = []
for i in tqdm(range(2, train.shape[1])):
    selector = RFE(estimator, n_features_to_select=i)
    selector = selector.fit(X, y)
    models.append(selector)
    Scores.append(selector.score(X, y))
